This article is a presidential proclamation by President Barack Obama on the 45th anniversary of Medicare and Medicaid. The proclamation highlights the importance of these programs in providing healthcare coverage for millions of Americans, particularly seniors and low-income individuals. It emphasizes the need to ensure the trust and support between the government and its citizens remains strong. The proclamation also mentions the Affordable Care Act (ACA) and its role in renewing and strengthening Medicare and Medicaid, including extending the life of the Medicare trust fund and addressing overpayments to insurance companies. The ACA also aims to provide greater savings, improved quality, and increased accountability in healthcare coverage. The proclamation concludes by urging all Americans to observe the day with appropriate ceremonies and activities to recognize the vital safety net that Medicare and Medicaid provide.